Class MapAdapterPopulatedTests

java.lang.Object
myTest.MapAdapterPopulatedTests
public class MapAdapterPopulatedTests extends Object
This test case tests the MapAdapter class in a populated state. Every method of the MapAdapter class is tested to ensure the class implementation is correct for populated maps. For each method tests are created to ensure correct behavior in normal and edge cases, including correct throw of exceptions and correct return values.
See Also:
  • MapAdapter
Design
This test case aims to verify the correct behavior of populated MapAdapter instances to ensure it correctly implements the HMap interface.
Libraries
JUnit 4.13, Hamcrest 1.3

    • setUp

      public void setUp()
      Sets up the test environment by creating a MapAdapter instance and populating it with 100 entries, where keys are "key0" to "key99" and values are "value0" to "value49" (values repeat every 50 keys) to ensure correct behavior with duplicate values.

    • testClear

      public void testClear()
      Tests that the MapAdapter.clear() method call on a populated map leaves the map empty.
      Design
      The test aims to verify that the MapAdapter.clear() method call on an populated map empties the map when called on an populated map.
      Description
      The MapAdapter.clear() method is called on the populated map created in the setUp() method. After the call the map is tested to be empty by asserting that MapAdapter.isEmpty() returns true and the size is 0.
      Preconditions
      The map is correctly instantiated and populated
      Postconditions
      The map is empty
      Expected Results
      The map is empty after the MapAdapter.clear() method call.

    • testContainsValueNull

      public void testContainsValueNull()
      Tests that the MapAdapter.containsValue(Object) throws NullPointerException when called with null argument.
      Design
      The test aims to verify that the MapAdapter.containsValue(Object) method throws NullPointerException when called with null argument.
      Description
      The MapAdapter.containsValue(Object) method is called with null argument on the map created by the setUp() method. Since the map does not accept null values, the method should throw NullPointerException.
      Preconditions
      The map is correctly instantiated
      Postconditions
      The map is unchanged
      Expected Results
      The MapAdapter.containsValue(Object) method throws NullPointerException when called with null argument.

    • testContainsValueNotPresent

      public void testContainsValueNotPresent()
      Tests that the MapAdapter.containsValue(Object) method returns false when called with a value not present in the map.
      Design
      The test aims to verify that the MapAdapter.containsValue(Object) method returns false when called on a populated map with a value not present.
      Description
      The MapAdapter.containsValue(Object) method is called with a value not present (for this test the string "test" is used) on the populated map created by the setUp() method. Since the map is populated with values "value0" to "value49" (repeating), the result of the method is asserted to be false.
      Preconditions
      The map is correctly instantiated and populated; "test" is not a value in the map.
      Postconditions
      The map is unchanged
      Expected Results
      The MapAdapter.containsValue(Object) method returns false when called with a value not present in the map.

      Tests that the MapAdapter.get(Object) method returns the value associated with a key present in the map.
      Design
      The test aims to verify that the MapAdapter.get(Object) method returns the value associated with the key when it is present at the start of the map.
      Description
      The MapAdapter.get(Object) method is called with a key present at start (for this test the starting key "key0" is used) on the map created by the setUp() method.       Postconditions
      The map is unchanged.
